---
layout: layouts/base-finpay.njk
title: "401(k) Self-Directed Brokerage Account Management | SDBA Advisor"
description: "Professional management of your 401(k) SDBA / brokerage window. Access thousands of investments with fiduciary guidance. Capital Wealth, Lehi, UT."
breadcrumbs:
  - { name: "Home", url: "/" }
  - { name: "Services", url: "/services/" }
  - { name: "SDBA", url: "/services/sdba/" }
  - { name: "401(k) Brokerage Window", url: "/services/sdba/401k-brokerage-window/" }
faqSchema:
  - question: "How do I know if my plan has an SDBA?"
    answer: "Check your plan website or call your plan administrator. Look for terms like 'brokerage window,' 'BrokerageLink,' 'PCRA,' or 'self-directed option.' If you're not sure, we can help you find out."
  - question: "What's the difference between SDBA and rolling over to an IRA?"
    answer: "With an SDBA, your money stays in your employer plan. You keep potential benefits like creditor protection, plan loan access, and often lower institutional share class pricing. A rollover moves money out entirely — which may be better in some cases. We help you compare both."
  - question: "Can Capital Wealth manage my 401(k) directly?"
    answer: "Through the SDBA, yes. The brokerage window creates a channel for us to build and manage a professional portfolio inside your plan. Without the SDBA, most advisors can't touch your employer plan."
  - question: "Are there extra fees?"
    answer: "SDBA accounts typically charge an annual maintenance fee ($25-$50/year), plus the expense ratios of the funds selected. We analyze all fees to ensure they're justified by the improved investment strategy."
