      <span class="ep-chapter-label">Common Questions</span>
      <h2 class="ep-faq-title">401(k) Window FAQ</h2>
      <p class="ep-faq-sub">The most common questions employees have about brokerage windows in their workplace retirement plans.</p>
      <a href="/contact/" class="ep-btn-ghost">Ask About Your Plan</a>
    </div>
    <div>
      <button class="ep-faq-item" onclick="this.classList.toggle('active')">
        <span class="ep-faq-q">How do I know if my plan has an SDBA? <span class="ep-faq-icon">+</span></span>
        <div class="ep-faq-a"><p>Check your plan website or call your plan administrator. Look for terms like "brokerage window," "BrokerageLink," "PCRA," or "self-directed option." If you're not sure, we can help you find out.</p></div>
      </button>
      <button class="ep-faq-item" onclick="this.classList.toggle('active')">
        <span class="ep-faq-q">What's the difference between SDBA and rolling over to an IRA? <span class="ep-faq-icon">+</span></span>
        <div class="ep-faq-a"><p>With an SDBA, your money stays in your employer plan. You keep potential benefits like creditor protection, plan loan access, and often lower institutional share class pricing. A rollover moves money out entirely — which may be better in some cases. We help you compare both.</p></div>
      </button>
      <button class="ep-faq-item" onclick="this.classList.toggle('active')">
        <span class="ep-faq-q">Can Capital Wealth manage my 401(k) directly? <span class="ep-faq-icon">+</span></span>
        <div class="ep-faq-a"><p>Through the SDBA, yes. The brokerage window creates a channel for us to build and manage a professional portfolio inside your plan. Without the SDBA, most advisors can't touch your employer plan.</p></div>
      </button>
      <button class="ep-faq-item" onclick="this.classList.toggle('active')">
        <span class="ep-faq-q">Are there extra fees? <span class="ep-faq-icon">+</span></span>
        <div class="ep-faq-a"><p>SDBA accounts typically charge an annual maintenance fee ($25-$50/year), plus the expense ratios of the funds selected. We analyze all fees to ensure they're justified by the improved investment strategy.</p></div>
      </button>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

